```

## tables

tables are of the form `#<delimiter>{}`. Delimiters can be multi-character.

The first row becomes the table header. Each item is trimmed of its whitespace

#,{
name, statically typed, GC, compiled
Go, yes, yes, yes
Zig, yes, no, yes
Python, no, yes, no
}

## custom blocks

custom blocks are of the form `function:{input}`

Different translators will have different built-in functions. To run shell commands, prefix the function with `!`. Some translators have a secure mode that forbids these.

## metadata

you can specify metadata in a ''@{}'' block, as key-value pairs of strings. These can be used by static site generators, Wikis and other programs

They need to be of the form `key = value`. Whitespace is trimmed

Additionaly, the shortcut ''=#'' exists which creates a `h1` element with its argument ==and== sets the ''title'' attribute to the content
